  <prompt>
    Extend the `FilePreviewContextWidget` (task 018) with a per-file "Summarize this only"
    button affordance — this is the FR-08 UI path counterpart to the FR-08 LLM tool-call
    path (where the agent calls `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` from task 015 with a single
    `fileIds: [singleFile]`). Each file card in the widget's multi-file list (and the
    single-file inline preview header) renders a button. Click dispatches directly to the
    `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` via either the direct endpoint (task 014
    `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/summarize` with `fileIds: [singleFileId]`) OR
    the agent-tool path (task 015) — pick ONE dispatch route explicitly per spec FR-08;
    the direct endpoint is the simpler choice and matches the slash-command parity story.
    The invocation MUST produce a NEW Workspace tab (additive); the PRIOR tab containing
    any previous Summarize result MUST remain untouched (FR-06 tab additivity + FR-08
    multi-turn refinement). PaneEventBus dispatch emits `workspace.streaming_started`
    (R5 additive event type from task 016) to signal new-tab creation to the
    `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 017).

    Multi-turn refinement: each "Summarize this only" click is its own conversation turn
    and produces a fresh, isolated Workspace tab. The user can continue chatting in the
    Assistant pane to refine the single-file output (e.g., "make that more concise",
    "translate to Spanish") — the chat conversation continues against the newly-opened
    tab as its anchor.

    R5 is configuration-first and reuse-first: this task EXTENDS task 018's
    `FilePreviewContextWidget` (does NOT fork a parallel widget per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1
    reuse mandate), reuses the existing dispatch path established by tasks 014 + 016 + 017
    (does NOT introduce a new orchestrator path), and adds ZERO new PaneEventBus channels
    (per ADR-030 — only emits the additive event types already added by task 016). Fluent
    UI v9 semantic tokens; dark-mode tested; React 19.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React + Fluent UI v9 developer with deep familiarity of:
    - `FilePreviewContextWidget` (task 018) and the extracted `RichFilePreview` renderer
      (task 013)
    - `@spaarke/ai-widgets` PaneEventBus dispatch via `useDispatchPaneEvent` hook
    - SSE consumption from BFF AI endpoints (`POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize`,
      task 014) via the existing `authenticatedFetch` + EventSource pattern
    - Workspace tab lifecycle: `workspace.widget_load` dispatch produces additive tabs
      consumed by `WorkspacePane` per ADR-030 + R4/R5 Workspace architecture
    - Fluent UI v9 component patterns (`Button`, `Tooltip`, `MenuItem`, semantic tokens,
      dark-mode parity)
    Familiar with R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate, §3.4 PaneEventBus additive event-type
    discipline, and the FULL-rigor task-execute protocol per CLAUDE.md §4.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `FilePreviewContextWidget` (task 018) is extended with a "Summarize this only" button
    affordance rendered on EVERY file card in the multi-file list AND on the single-file
    inline preview header. Click handler dispatches a single-file Summarize invocation via
    the chosen path (default: direct endpoint `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/summarize`
    with body `{ fileIds: [singleFileId] }`) AND emits a `workspace.streaming_started`
    PaneEventBus event (task 016 additive event type within the existing `workspace`
    channel) that signals to `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 017) to mount as a NEW
    Workspace tab. Prior Workspace tabs (any earlier multi-file or single-file Summarize
    output) are preserved unchanged — additive-only per FR-06.

    Multi-turn refinement works: user clicks "Summarize this only" on file A → new tab
    mounts → streaming completes → user types "make that more concise" in Assistant pane
    → chat continues against that new tab; user clicks "Summarize this only" on file B
    → ANOTHER new tab mounts; file A's tab remains. Tab count is bounded by the existing
    `MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS` ≈ 8 FIFO eviction policy (FR-06).

    The button is keyboard accessible (Enter / Space activates), screen-reader labeled
    (`aria-label="Summarize this file only"`), dark-mode tested (Fluent v9 semantic
    tokens — never raw hex/rgb), and rendered using `Button` (icon + label OR icon-only
    with `Tooltip` for compact mode — choose explicitly per Step 3 design decision).

    All quality gates pass at Step 9.5. Acceptance criteria below all green.
  </goal>

