  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate">MUST EXTEND `FilePreviewContextWidget` from task 018; MUST NOT create a parallel widget. Reuse the extracted `RichFilePreview` renderer (task 013) and the existing file card layout from task 018. If the click handler's HTTP-call boilerplate already exists in a shared helper (e.g., `summarizeService.ts` in SpaarkeAi or LegalWorkspace), reuse it — otherwise add the helper to `@spaarke/ai-widgets` services and reuse from task 020's chat-pane dispatch site.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 prohibited list">MUST NOT introduce a parallel SSE envelope to `AnalysisChunk` (rendering inherits from task 017's `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`). MUST NOT introduce a parallel chat agent (this task is UI-only; the LLM tool-call path remains task 015's responsibility).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 — use modern React patterns (no legacy class components, no `useEffect`-for-everything anti-pattern). Click handler is a `useCallback` memoized closure. State (e.g., per-file "summarizing in progress" indicator) is local component state.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 components only — `Button`, `Tooltip`, `MenuItem`, `Spinner`. Semantic tokens only (e.g., `tokens.colorBrandBackground`, `tokens.colorNeutralForeground1`) — NEVER raw hex / rgb. Dark-mode parity verified (use `useTheme` if differentiation is needed).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030 + R5 CLAUDE.md §3.4">PaneEventBus is closed at 4 channels — MUST NOT add a 5th. The dispatch from this task emits `workspace.streaming_started` (additive event type within the existing `workspace` channel, added by task 016). Subscribers (`StructuredOutputStreamWidget` task 017) consume the event and mount a new tab. Use the existing `useDispatchPaneEvent` hook.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">New code lives in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` (the FilePreviewContextWidget package). If a shared single-file Summarize service helper is introduced, it lives in `@spaarke/ai-widgets/services/` (preferred) or a colocated module — NOT in a new top-level shared library.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-08 (UI path)">"Summarize this only" button per file card; click dispatches single-file Summarize and produces a NEW Workspace tab. PRIOR tabs MUST remain unaffected. The UI-path counterpart of the same FR-08 LLM tool-call path (task 015) — both produce additive tabs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-06 (additive tabs)">New tab opens via dispatch on `workspace.widget_load` (existing channel) OR via the `workspace.streaming_started` additive event type from task 016 that the `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 017) subscribes to. EXISTING tabs are NOT modified or replaced. FIFO eviction at `MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS` cap applies; brief toast notifies on eviction. Verify the streaming-tab and any prior tabs co-exist in the Workspace tab strip via integration smoke test.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-08 (multi-turn refinement)">Each "Summarize this only" click is a NEW conversation turn anchored to the new tab. User can continue chatting in the Assistant pane against this new tab. This task wires the button + dispatch; the conversation-anchoring logic is owned by the `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 017) + chat-pane (task 020). This task MUST NOT mutate any existing tab's state when invoked.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-05 (DocumentRowMenu reuse)">The per-file card already exposes a 3-dot menu reusing the existing `DocumentRowMenu` from `@spaarke/ui-components` (per task 018 acceptance) with 12 actions including `aiSummary`. The "Summarize this only" button is a PROMINENT primary affordance distinct from the menu — it does NOT replace the `aiSummary` menu item. Decision: keep both surfaces (button = single-file Summarize on this card; menu item = same action, alternative discovery). Document this overlap in implementation notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028 / R5 CLAUDE.md §9">No token snapshots. HTTP call to the direct endpoint uses the existing `@spaarke/auth` `useAuth()` + `authenticatedFetch` pattern; never capture the bearer token into a closure or React ref.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">If the HTTP dispatch fails, surface a Fluent v9 `MessageBar` (or equivalent transient notification) reading the `errorCode` + `detail` from the ProblemDetails response (returned by task 014's endpoint). NEVER leak raw stack traces or document content.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 / bff-extensions §F test obligation">PRs touching `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/context/FilePreviewContextWidget.tsx` MUST add/update component tests. Add `FilePreviewContextWidget.summarize-only.test.tsx` (or extend the test file added in task 018) covering: button renders per file card, click dispatches the expected HTTP call + PaneEventBus event, prior-tab state unchanged, dark-mode rendering.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-07 / R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6">This task is frontend-only. BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (no BFF code change). Confirm in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-02">File count enforced at Assistant-pane upload (≤ 20 per session). This task does not need additional file-count validation — it operates on already-staged files from `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Path-drift correction: spec.md/plan.md reference `infra/ai-search/`; ACTUAL repo path is `infrastructure/ai-search/`. This task is frontend-only and does not touch ai-search paths, but observe the correction when referencing infra in implementation notes.</constraint>
  </constraints>

