    <patterns>
      <pattern name="`useDispatchPaneEvent` for cross-pane dispatch (canonical)" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/useDispatchPaneEvent.ts">
        Per ADR-030 the standard dispatch hook. Example usage:
        ```tsx
        const dispatch = useDispatchPaneEvent();
        const onSummarizeOnly = useCallback(() => {
          dispatch('workspace', {
            type: 'streaming_started',
            sessionId,
            requestId: crypto.randomUUID(),
            widgetType: 'structured-output-stream',
            inputs: { fileIds: [fileId], style: 'default' },
          });
        }, [dispatch, sessionId, fileId]);
        ```
        Verify the EXACT shape of the `workspace.streaming_started` payload by reading
        task 016's POML output before writing this code — the discriminant fields are
        defined there.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Direct endpoint POST with `authenticatedFetch` + SSE consumption" location="src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/summarizeService.ts">
        Canonical SSE consumption pattern: `authenticatedFetch` (from `@spaarke/auth`)
        opens a POST request, the body iterates via `getReader()` on the response stream,
        each chunk is split on `\n\n` and parsed as a `data: {json}` SSE event, and the
        events are forwarded to a callback. R5 task 017's `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`
        owns the actual SSE-consumption rendering; this task's click handler may either
        (a) directly call this service helper, OR (b) just emit the
        `workspace.streaming_started` event and let the widget handle SSE opening itself
        (cleaner separation). Pick (b) for clean separation of concerns; the
        StructuredOutputStreamWidget already subscribes to streaming_started per task 017.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="File card layout from FilePreviewContextWidget (task 018)" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/context/FilePreviewContextWidget.tsx">
        Task 018 ships the file card layout for multi-file mode + the inline single-file
        preview. Extension surface: add a `Button` (or `MenuButton` if reusing
        `DocumentRowMenu`'s aiSummary path) PER file card. Position: top-right of the
        card adjacent to the existing 3-dot menu trigger. Single-file mode: button
        appears in the preview header next to the 3-dot menu and prev/next controls.
        Confirm task 018's exact JSX entry points before editing — task 018 lands first
        per P2-G4 → P2-G5 wave ordering.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 Button with Tooltip + semantic tokens" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/DocumentRowMenu.tsx">
        Canonical Button + Tooltip composition pattern. Mirror for the "Summarize this only"
        button:
        ```tsx
        &lt;Tooltip content="Summarize this file only" relationship="label"&gt;
          &lt;Button
            icon={&lt;DocumentTextRegular /&gt;}
            appearance="subtle"
            aria-label="Summarize this file only"
            onClick={onSummarizeOnly}
          /&gt;
        &lt;/Tooltip&gt;
        ```
        Semantic tokens only — never raw color literals. If a "summarizing in progress"
        state needs visual feedback, swap icon to `&lt;Spinner size="extra-tiny" /&gt;`
        until streaming_complete arrives back from the workspace pane (optional —
        coordinate with task 017's widget which is the single source of truth for the
        in-flight indicator).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="DocumentRowMenu aiSummary action (existing parallel surface)" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/DocumentRowMenu.tsx">
        DocumentRowMenu already exposes 12 actions including `aiSummary`. If task 018
        wires `aiSummary` to dispatch the SAME event this button emits, the button + menu
        share a single click handler. Recommended: extract a shared
        `useSummarizeOnly(fileId, sessionId)` hook in the widget file scope; both the
        button and the menu item invoke it.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Workspace tab additivity (FR-06 + R4 OC-R4-05)" location="docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md">
        Workspace pane subscribes to `workspace.widget_load` (and additively, the R5 new
        `streaming_started` discriminant) and PUSHES a new tab onto its tab strip;
        existing tabs are not mutated. FIFO eviction at `MAX_WORKSPACE_TABS` ≈ 8 with a
        brief toast. This task does not implement tab management — it dispatches the
        event and relies on the existing workspace tab subscriber.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 ships a chat-driven "Summarize a Document" vertical slice. After multi-file
      Summarize completes (initial flow), users frequently want to re-focus on a single
      file ("just summarize file 2", "give me a TL;DR of contract A only"). Spec FR-08
      mandates BOTH a natural-language path (LLM tool-call via `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool`
      from task 015 — "summarize just file 2") AND an explicit UI affordance ("Summarize
      this only" button per file card in the Context pane). Both paths converge on the
      same `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (task 012) and both produce additive Workspace
      tabs (FR-06). This task wires the UI affordance.

      The button is small in scope (3 hours estimated) but high in user-perceived value
      — single-file refinement is a primary multi-turn use case during legal review.
      The implementation is straightforward because tasks 018 (widget structure), 016
      (event types), and 017 (target widget) have done the supporting work.

      Two parallel-surface decisions exist (documented in implementation notes per Step 3):
      (1) explicit "Summarize this only" Button vs. menu-only via DocumentRowMenu
      `aiSummary`. We keep BOTH per spec FR-05 (DocumentRowMenu reuse mandate); the
      button is the prominent primary affordance, the menu item is alternative discovery.
      (2) dispatch path: direct HTTP call OR PaneEventBus emit. We prefer PaneEventBus
      emit (`workspace.streaming_started` from task 016) for cleaner separation — the
      `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 017) is the single SSE consumer and owns
      tab-mounting + streaming render. The click handler emits the event and is done.
    </background>
