    <step order="3" name="Implementation Plan + Two Open Decisions">
      Make TWO explicit decisions and document them in task notes:

      Decision A (dispatch path):
      Option A1 — PaneEventBus-only: button click emits `workspace.streaming_started`
                   and is done; `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 017) opens the
                   tab AND opens the SSE connection itself. Cleaner separation;
                   recommended.
      Option A2 — Direct HTTP + event: button click both calls
                   `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/summarize` directly AND emits
                   the PaneEventBus event with a sessionId/requestId binding. Avoid
                   unless task 017's subscriber design requires it.

      Decision B (button vs menu vs both):
      Option B1 — Both (RECOMMENDED): prominent `Button` per file card + existing
                   `DocumentRowMenu` `aiSummary` action. Share a
                   `useSummarizeOnly(fileId, sessionId)` hook.
      Option B2 — Button-only.
      Option B3 — Menu-only.

      Recommended: A1 + B1. Record the chosen options in task notes and proceed.

      Identify the EXACT JSX insertion points in task 018's `FilePreviewContextWidget`:
      - Multi-file mode: file card top-right action area (adjacent to 3-dot menu)
      - Single-file mode: preview header action area (adjacent to 3-dot menu +
        prev/next controls)
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement `useSummarizeOnly` Hook + Button">
      Create or extend
      `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/context/FilePreviewContextWidget.tsx`
      to add:

      (a) A local hook `useSummarizeOnly(fileId, sessionId, fileName)` that returns
          `{ onClick, isInFlight }`. Implementation per Decision A1:
          ```tsx
          const useSummarizeOnly = (fileId: string, sessionId: string, fileName: string) =&gt; {
            const dispatch = useDispatchPaneEvent();
            const [isInFlight, setInFlight] = useState(false);
            const onClick = useCallback(() =&gt; {
              setInFlight(true);
              dispatch('workspace', {
                type: 'streaming_started',
                sessionId,
                requestId: crypto.randomUUID(),
                widgetType: 'structured-output-stream',
                inputs: {
                  fileIds: [fileId],
                  style: 'default',
                  displayName: `Summary: ${fileName}`,
                },
              });
              // isInFlight resets on workspace.streaming_complete from task 017
              // (subscribed via usePaneEvent in this widget — see Step 4(c))
            }, [dispatch, sessionId, fileId, fileName]);
            return { onClick, isInFlight };
          };
          ```
          Conform the event payload to the EXACT shape established by task 016.

      (b) Subscribe to `workspace.streaming_complete` in the widget to reset the
          per-file `isInFlight` state when the matching `requestId` completes (optional
          polish; recommended for clarity).

      (c) Render a `Button` (Fluent v9; semantic tokens; `aria-label`) per file card:
          ```tsx
          &lt;Tooltip content="Summarize this file only" relationship="label"&gt;
            &lt;Button
              icon={isInFlight ? &lt;Spinner size="extra-tiny" /&gt; : &lt;DocumentTextRegular /&gt;}
              appearance="subtle"
              aria-label={`Summarize ${file.name} only`}
              disabled={isInFlight}
              onClick={onSummarizeOnly}
            /&gt;
          &lt;/Tooltip&gt;
          ```
          Render this button in BOTH the multi-file card layout AND the single-file
          preview header.

      (d) Wire the same `useSummarizeOnly` hook into the existing `DocumentRowMenu`
          `aiSummary` menu item callback if task 018 left it as a TODO / placeholder —
          this satisfies the FR-05 alternative-discovery path and matches Decision B1.

      Verify dark-mode parity by inspecting in Fluent v9 dark theme (no hex colors,
      tokens only).
    </step>
