    <criterion testable="true">"Summarize this only" Button renders on EVERY file card in `FilePreviewContextWidget`'s multi-file mode AND on the inline preview header in single-file mode. Confirmed by Step 5 Test 1.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Clicking the button dispatches a `workspace.streaming_started` PaneEventBus event with `fileIds: [singleFileId]`, the active `sessionId`, and a unique `requestId`. Payload shape matches task 016's event-type definition exactly. Confirmed by Step 5 Test 2.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Click produces a NEW Workspace tab (additive). PRIOR Workspace tabs (e.g., a previous multi-file Summarize tab) remain present and unchanged in content. Confirmed by Step 5 Test 3 + end-to-end smoke Step 8(d–f).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Multi-turn refinement works: each click of "Summarize this only" on a different file produces another additive tab; user can continue chatting in the Assistant pane to refine each tab's output (verified via end-to-end smoke Step 8(g) — this task is responsible for ensuring its dispatch does NOT prevent that downstream behavior).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`DocumentRowMenu` `aiSummary` menu item (existing per task 018) dispatches the SAME event as the new button via the shared `useSummarizeOnly` hook (Decision B1). Confirmed by Step 5 Test 4.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PaneEventBus integrity: zero new channels added (still 4: `workspace`, `context`, `conversation`, `safety`); zero new event-type discriminants added by this task (only emits the `workspace.streaming_started` type already added by task 016). ADR-030 compliance confirmed by Step 6 static-scan.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Button is keyboard accessible (Enter / Space triggers click); `aria-label` includes the file name; in-flight state renders a `Spinner` and disables the button; on receipt of matching `workspace.streaming_complete`, button returns to interactive state. Confirmed by Step 5 Tests 5 + 6.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Fluent UI v9 + semantic tokens only (no raw hex / rgb literals); dark-mode parity verified. ADR-021 compliance confirmed by Step 5 Test 7.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">React 19 patterns: handlers memoized via `useCallback`; in-flight state via local component state; no legacy class components; no unnecessary `useEffect`. ADR-022 compliance confirmed at Step 9.5 `adr-check`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No token snapshot per ADR-028: if Decision A2 was chosen, HTTP call uses `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`; tokens are not captured into a closure or ref. Confirmed at Step 9.5 `adr-check`. (If Decision A1 — PaneEventBus-only — no HTTP call is made by this widget; ADR-028 N/A but documented.)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Build clean: `npm run build` zero errors; `npm run lint` zero new errors; all 7 component tests pass. Confirmed at Steps 7 + 8.</criterion>
